htw.vs1.filesystem.FileSystem.virtual

Interface FSObject

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    File, Folder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFSObject, LocalFile, LocalFolder, LocalFSObject, MountPointFolder, RemoteFile, RemoteFolder, RemoteFSObject

    public interface FSObject
    A FSObject represents a object in our filesystem. It can either be a Folder, which can contain other FSObjects, or a File, which is a leaf of the filesystem. Created by markus on 01.06.15.
